  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Defocus in cathode lens instruments</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-06</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Defocus plays an important role in cathode lens microscope image analysis. • Methods to measure defocus are reviewed. • Defocus measurements by sample shift are analyzed analytically and numerically. • Such measurements are applied to energy dependent defocus measurements in an aberration corrected instrument and compared with theory. • We also explain previous observations in the MnAs system.</subfield>
